{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
    "chapterNumber": 1,
    "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1",
    "summary": "Source text for Ecclesiastes 1 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:1",
      "text": "The words of the Preacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:2",
      "text": "Vanity of vanities, says the Preacher, vanity of vanities! All is vanity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:3",
      "text": "What does man gain by all the toil at which he toils under the sun?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:4",
      "text": "A generation goes, and a generation comes, but the earth remains for ever.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:5",
      "text": "The sun rises and the sun goes down, and hastens to the place where it rises.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:6",
      "text": "The wind blows to the south, and goes round to the north; round and round goes the wind, and on its circuits the wind returns.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:7",
      "text": "All streams run to the sea, but the sea is not full; to the place where the streams flow, there they flow again.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:8",
      "text": "All things are full of weariness; a man cannot utter it; the eye is not satisfied with seeing, nor the ear filled with hearing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:9",
      "text": "What has been is what will be, and what has been done is what will be done; and there is nothing new under the sun.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:10",
      "text": "Is there a thing of which it is said, “See, this is new”? It has been already, in the ages before us.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:11",
      "text": "There is no remembrance of former things, nor will there be any remembrance of later things yet to happen among those who come after.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:12",
      "text": "I the Preacher have been king over Israel in Jerusalem.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:13",
      "text": "And I applied my mind to seek and to search out by wisdom all that is done under heaven; it is an unhappy business that God has given to the sons of men to be busy with.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:14",
      "text": "I have seen everything that is done under the sun; and behold, all is vanity and a striving after wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:15",
      "text": "What is crooked cannot be made straight, and what is lacking cannot be numbered.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:16",
      "text": "I said to myself, “I have acquired great wisdom, surpassing all who were over Jerusalem before me; and my mind has had great experience of wisdom and knowledge.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:17",
      "text": "And I applied my mind to know wisdom and to know madness and folly. I perceived that this also is but a striving after wind.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.1.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 1,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 1:18",
      "text": "For in much wisdom is much vexation, and he who increases knowledge increases sorrow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
